600 grams Potatoes
150 grams Broccolini
320 grams Irish Chicken Breast
2 sachet(s) Thai Style Spice Mix
1 sachet(s) Teriyaki Sauce
2 sachet(s) Mayo
to taste Oil
to taste Salt
to taste Pepper

Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.
Chop the potatoes into 2cm chunks (peeling optional). Pop onto a large (lined) baking tray.
Toss with half the Thai spice, salt, pepper, and a drizzle of oil. Spread out in a single layer.
When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, 25-35 mins. Turn the tray halfway through.

Meanwhile, lay the chicken on a separate lined baking tray.
Toss with remaining Thai spice mix, salt, pepper and a drizzle of oil. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
Roast on the middle shelf of the oven until cooked through, 25-30 mins.
TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? Don’t worry, this is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

When the chicken has been in the oven for 15 mins,  toss the broccolini with a drizzle of oil and season with salt and pepper.
Pop onto the tray alongside the chicken.
Spread the teriyaki sauce over the chicken.
Return to the oven for the remaining time, 10-15 mins.

Once cooked, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm thick slices, then divide between plates.
Spoon over any excess teriyaki sauce from the tray.
Serve with potatoes and roasted broccolini alongside.
Finish with a dollop of mayo.